{"metadata":{"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Authentication Flow","type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":", which contained the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters: now, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"type":"text","text":" holds all instances of the "},{"code":"struct","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":", but have moved to default implementations of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`","type":"heading","anchor":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned previously, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration"},{"text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and requires a ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"level":2,"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","type":"heading","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit":{"url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Develop and manage client and server-side applications for the AT Protocol and Bluesky."}],"type":"topic","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"atprotokit_icon.png"}],"role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit","kind":"symbol","title":"ATProtoKit"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/getSession()":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/getsession()","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"getSession()","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"k